---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'How is this different from hiring three separate agencies?',
    a: 'One team, one strategy, one P&L. When SEO, paid, content, and lifecycle live under the same roof, insights move sideways and the work compounds. Three agencies means three roadmaps, three reports, and three reasons your numbers do not add up at the end of the quarter.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How quickly will I see results?',
    a: 'Paid channels typically show signal in the first 30 days and stabilize by 60 to 90. SEO and content compound over 4 to 9 months. We set 30, 60, and 90 day targets in the kickoff plan so progress is checked against numbers, not feelings.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do I need a working website first?',
    a: 'Marketing into a broken site burns money. If your site is leaking conversion, we either fix the critical pages first or run our Website Design engagement alongside the growth program. We will tell you which after the audit.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does the engagement look like month to month?',
    a: 'A weekly working session, a shared roadmap, and a monthly review that ties channel performance back to pipeline. You always know what is shipping this week, what is being tested, and what the spend bought you last month.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do you handle AI search and Generative Engine Optimization?',
    a: 'GEO is built into every content brief, every page, and every release. We optimize for entity recognition, semantic structure, and answer formats so your brand earns citations in ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews, not just position 1 in classic search.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Who owns the accounts, data, and creative?',
    a: 'You do. Ad accounts, analytics, CRM, creative assets, content libraries - all in your name, all handed over from day one. If you ever leave, you walk away with the whole system intact.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does it cost?',
    a: 'Engagements typically start in the mid four figures per month and scale with channel scope and ad spend. We send a fixed-fee proposal after the audit so you know exactly what you are paying for - and what pipeline target it is built to hit - before we begin.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="relative bg-black py-24 text-white md:py-32">
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 bg-grid-dark opacity-30 [mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse_at_center,black_30%,transparent_75%)]"></div>
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-32 top-1/3 h-96 w-96 rounded-full bg-gold/10 blur-3xl"></div>

  <div class="container-x relative">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gold-soft">
        <span class="h-px w-6 bg-gold-soft"></span>
        FAQ
      </span>
      <h2 class="mt-5 font-display text-4xl font-medium leading-[1.05] tracking-tight md:text-6xl">
        Growth questions, answered.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-xl text-base text-white/65 md:text-lg">
        The things prospects ask us most before kicking off a marketing engagement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-3xl divide-y divide-white/10 border-y border-white/10">
      {faqs.map((f) => (
        <details class="group faq-item">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-start justify-between gap-6 py-6 transition-colors hover:text-gold-soft md:py-7">
            <span class="font-display text-lg font-medium leading-snug md:text-xl">{f.q}</span>
            <span class="mt-1 flex h-7 w-7 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-white/15 text-gold-soft transition-all duration-300 group-open:rotate-45 group-open:border-gold-soft/60 group-open:bg-gold-soft/10" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" class="h-3 w-3">
                <path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="pb-6 pr-12 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/65 md:pb-7 md:text-base">{f.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-item[open] summary { color: rgb(224 198 123 / 0.95); }
</style>
